==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hawk-eyed
<hw>Hawk"-eyed`</hw> <pr>(-⟦imac⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having
very keen vision; sharp-sighted; discerning.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> keen-sighted, lynx-eyed, quick-sighted, sharp-eyed,
sharp-sighted.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>alert to possible danger.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> argus-eyed, open-eyed, unsleeping, vigilant, wary,
watchful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hawkeye State</ent>⟦br⟧
